<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-577-830  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 577 830.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  August 14 1989 n551 p35(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Relays take up automation baton. (Market shifts to high-volumestandard products)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Derman, Glenda.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A rapidly growing market and growing global competition is forcingUS relay makers to employ more automation, improve reliability,reduce costs, optimize design-to-market productivity, and embracenew technologies to remain competitive.andP;  Statistical processcontrol and total quality programs are being implemented toachieve zero-defect reliability.andP;  Surface-mount technology (SMT)is slowly penetrating the relay market, but a volume SMT market isstill at least two years off.andP;  Trends in electromechanical relays,high-power devices, reed relays (including mercury-wetted reeddevices), and solid state relays are discussed.andP;  Exemplifyingproducts are described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     RelaysTrendsProduct DevelopmentRequirements AnalysisApplicationsProductsSpecifications.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>